notes: On 28 March 2023, in San Joaquin (Carabobo), municipal police forces shot and killed a teenage boy while he was collecting scrap metal inside the premises of a company. The boy was taken to hospital for treatment, but was pronounced dead a day later. According to the police the victim was armed, and claim that his killing happened during an armed confrontation. Residents and relatives disagree with this version and argue that a group of scrap metal collectors, including the unarmed victim, had received authorization from a security guard and the owner of the place to enter the premises; it is thought that another security guard was not informed of this authorized entry, and alerted the police officers, who arrived on scene thinking that the venue had been trespassed by thieves. Relatives of the victim and residents demonstrated on 30 March to demand justice for him (coded separately). 1 fatality.

notes: On 24 March 2023, in Irapa (Sucre), PNB police and other unspecified security forces (coded as GNB) clashed with members of the El Conejo Gang, killing their leader, during a two-hour armed confrontation with multiple suspects which occurred in the early hours of the day. Police and intelligence forces had followed the gang members as they fled Aragua state, following the arrest of the Santos Michelena mayor for links with this criminal group earlier this week. An entourage of at least 35 armed suspects had helped the gang leader bypass security checkpoints along the way. The gang leader, and possibly 9 other people, including gang members and officers of the security forces were thought to have been killed during the armed confrontation, although this information was not confirmed. The leader of the gang was one of the top most wanted criminals in Venezuela, and was sought for numerous crimes, including homicide and extortion threats. The security forces arrested 36 people; and seized 16 firearms, seven grenades, nine cars, and 14 motorcycles. Around 10 fatalities.

On 21 March 2023, in Santa Ana de Coro (Falcon), three hooded members of the El Bisure Gang shot and killed a man, during an attack in an area close to the victim's home in the Cruz Verde neighborhood. The deceased, a lawyer, was thought to have been followed home from work by the perpetrators. The two other brothers of the deceased had also been executed by unidentified crime group suspects in separate attacks in the months prior to this attack (coded separately), presumably in retaliation over an unspecified incident with a criminal gang. The victim of this third attack had requested protection measures to the authorities. It was later established that the killing had been in retaliation, after the victim had provided the police with information on the whereabouts of a relative of one of the gang members. Five suspects were arrested a week later, including the three perpetrators. 1 fatality.

Around 9 March 2023 (as reported), in Pedro Maria Urena municipality (coded to Urena, Tachira), a man was shot and killed, and his body found by Colombian workers, floating in the Tachira River in an area known as the Cano Picho sector. It was established that the victim had been killed in Venezuelan territory, meters away from the border with Colombia, but his corpse was collected by the Colombian authorities nonetheless for humanitarian reasons. The identity of the perpetrators or the motivations for the killing are unknown, but it is suspected to be be related to operations of unidentified armed groups in the area which often use the area to dispose of bodies. 1 fatality.

notes: On 5 February 2023, in Las Tejerias (Aragua), approximately 30 armed members of the El Conejo Gang clashed with municipal police forces, during an attack on the local police station. The suspects employed assault weapons, detonated a grenade, and fired two mortar shells. Inside the police station there were 12 detainees, the authorities confirmed their wellbeing. GNB military and PNB police reinforcements were called on scene, forcing the gang members to fall back and seek refuge in a forested area outside the town. There is no further information on this armed confrontation at this point in time. Casualties are unknown.

This is one of the several clashes that have taken place during a special operation involving 1600 security personnel against gangs, in retaliation for the murder of a police officer and his wife on 4 September (coded separately) in Valles del Tuy valley. At least 23 people were killed, and 30 were arrested, including policemen throughout the operation carried out between 8 and 11 September. 2 fatalities.

notes: On 4 September 2022, in San Francisco de Yare (Miranda), suspected members of Carlos Capa Gang ambushed a police officer and his family, as they were driving back home after a family reunion. The suspects intercepted the vehicle and opened fire, killing the wife instantly, and injuring the officer and son. The policeman died six hours later in the ICU of Charavalle Hospital. In the shooting, the officer shot back and managed to injure one of his attackers, who was later arrested when seeking medical treatment. 2 fatalities.
